@page "/game-dev"

<PageTitle>Game Dev &mdash; Devon VanNote</PageTitle>

<section class="section-container">
    <h2 class="section-title">Game Dev</h2>

    <div class="gamedev-card">
        <div class="gamedev-header">
            <div>
                <h3 class="gamedev-title">
                    <a href="https://store.steampowered.com/app/1865260/Petrified/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
                        Petrified
                    </a>
                </h3>
                <p class="gamedev-subtitle">2D Asymmetrical Horror Game &mdash; Steam Deck Verified</p>
            </div>
            <a href="https://store.steampowered.com/app/1865260/Petrified/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="steam-btn">
                View on Steam &#8599;
            </a>
        </div>

        <p>
            Helped develop UI, audio, music, voice&nbsp;/&nbsp;text chat, and gameplay features for a 2D
            asymmetrical game built in Unity. The game pits players against each other in an asymmetrical
            horror experience and is verified for Steam Deck.
        </p>

        <div class="gamedev-sections">

            <div class="gamedev-section">
                <h4>UI &amp; Menus</h4>
                <p>
                    Developed all menus and in-game UI, including a player event log and a Steam friends list
                    display integrated directly into the game interface. All UI was built and verified for
                    Steam Deck input and display.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="gamedev-section">
                <h4>Voice &amp; Text Chat</h4>
                <p>
                    Integrated Vivox for in-game voice and text chat with on-screen indicators that show
                    which players are currently speaking during a match.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="gamedev-section">
                <h4>Multiplayer</h4>
                <p>
                    Leveraged Photon for networked multiplayer, including syncing player state and
                    in-game events across sessions.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="gamedev-section">
                <h4>Audio &amp; Music</h4>
                <p>
                    Contributed to the game's audio implementation and music integration to support
                    the horror atmosphere.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="gamedev-section">
                <h4>Gameplay &mdash; Camera Flip Powerup</h4>
                <p>
                    Created a powerup that flips the camera for 10 seconds, reversing player controls
                    and inverting all audio, adding a disorienting mechanic to gameplay.
                </p>
            </div>

        </div>

        <div class="gamedev-tags">
            <span class="skill-badge">Unity</span>
            <span class="skill-badge">C#</span>
            <span class="skill-badge">Vivox</span>
            <span class="skill-badge">Photon</span>
            <span class="skill-badge secondary">Steam</span>
            <span class="skill-badge secondary">Steam Deck</span>
        </div>
    </div>

</section>
